Title: Covariant actions for chiral supersymmetric bosons
Author: Kurt Lechner
Comments: 7 pages, Latex, no figures. Talk delivered at the Conference "Quantum
  Aspects of Gauge Theories, Supersymmetry and Unification", Neuchatel,
  Switzerland, September 1997
Journal-ref: Fortsch.Phys. 47 (1999) 209-216
\\
  We review a recently developed covariant Lagrangian formulation for
$p$--forms with (anti)self-dual field-strengths and present its extension to
the supersymmetric case. As explicit examples we construct covariant
Lagrangians for six-dimensional models with N=1 rigid and curved supersymmetry.
